### Describe the feature

Add support for the following commands across all language bindings (Java, Python, Node.js, Go):

- [`CLIENT PAUSE`](https://valkey.io/commands/client-pause/)
- [`CLIENT UNPAUSE`](https://valkey.io/commands/client-unpause/)

These commands are already defined in the Rust core layer but are not yet exposed in any of the language client APIs.

### Use Case

`CLIENT PAUSE` and `CLIENT UNPAUSE` are used during failover, maintenance windows, and data migration to temporarily halt client writes without dropping connections. This enables zero-downtime upgrades and safe slot migrations.

### Proposed Solution

Add command support for each language binding. The proposed APIs below are designed to be consistent with the compatible Redis clients (redis-py, Jedis, node-redis/ioredis, go-redis).

